The Chairman of Ikorodu Local Government, Mr Wasiu Adeshina, urged residents of the area to go and collect their permanent voter cards (PVC) in preparation for next yearâ€™s general elections. Speaking at a ceremony marking his first year in office, the council boss urged the people to take advantage of the ongoing voter registration exercise which would end on August 16. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Adeshina distributed free GCE forms to 60 candidates and announced scholarship awards to 60 others to mark his first year in office. Among dignitaries were Mr Babajimi Benson, member representing Ikorodu in the National Assembly, a former Deputy Governor, Mr Abiodun Ogunleye in Lagos and Ikorodu monarch, Oba Kabiru Shotobi.